definitions.definition: That which is or may be seized by animals to be devoured.
A person or thing given up as a victim.
A living thing, usually an animal, that is eaten by another living thing.
examples: The rabbit was eaten by the coyote, so the rabbit is the coyote's prey .
Stranded without any weapons, we made very easy prey .

definitions.definition: Anything, such as goods, etc., taken or got by violence; something taken by force from an enemy in war.
The act of devouring other creatures; ravage .
